{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f50bc8f2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Main Simulation: Educational virtual currency with RSA\n",
    "In this notebook, we simulate the lifecycle of a cryptocurrency transaction using the classes defined in our project.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1. Imports & Initialization\n",
    "We import:\n",
    "*   `Wallet`: to manage users and keys.\n",
    "*   `SimpleBlockchain` & `Transaction`: to manage the ledger and data.\n",
    "\n",
    "We then initialize the blockchain and create our two participants, **Alice** and **Bob**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a23da654",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from wallet import Wallet \n",
    "from blockchain import SimpleBlockchain, Transaction\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== EDUCATIONAL VIRTUAL CURRENCY WITH RSA ===\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Create blockchain instance\n",
    "blockchain = SimpleBlockchain()\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Create two users wallets\n",
    "print(\"1. Creating wallets...\")\n",
    "alice = Wallet(\"Alice\")\n",
    "bob = Wallet(\"Bob\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "05684535",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Identity Generation (RSA Keys)\n",
    "Before any transaction can happen, users must generate their **RSA Key Pairs**:\n",
    "*   **Private Key**: used to sign transactions (kept secret).\n",
    "*   **Public Key**: used as the wallet address (shared with the network).\n",
    "\n",
    "We then check their initial balance (which is 100 by default in the Wallet class)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ab27948f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 3. Generate RSA key pairs for both users\n",
    "# These keys are used to sign transactions and verify identity\n",
    "alice.generate_keys()\n",
    "bob.generate_keys()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n2. Alice has: {alice.balance} coin\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Bob has: {bob.balance} coin\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c113ab81",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. Mining the first block\n",
    "Alice decides to \"mine\" a block.\n",
    "By calling `mine_pending_transactions`, her computer solves the cryptographic puzzle (Proof of Work).\n",
    "*   **Reward**: as an incentive, the system rewards her with coins (simulated here by manually adding +10).\n",
    "*   **Result**: a new block is added to the blockchain."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a37c6644",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 4. Alice mines a block and receives a mining reward\n",
    "# In a real blockchain, mining confirms pending transactions\n",
    "print(\"\\n3. Alice mines a block...\")\n",
    "blockchain.mine_pending_transactions(alice.get_public_key_pem())\n",
    "alice.balance += 10 # Simplified mining reward simulation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c3866c4b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4. The Transaction (Alice -> Bob)\n",
    "This is the core security step.\n",
    "1.  **Creation**: we define who sends (Alice), who receives (Bob), and how much (5 coins).\n",
    "2.  **Signing**: Alice uses her **Private Key** to sign the transaction data. This generates a unique digital signature.\n",
    "3.  **Verification**: the system uses Alice's **Public Key** to verify that the signature is valid and the data hasn't been tampered with.\n",
    "\n",
    "If valid, the transaction is added to the \"Pending Pool\"."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b33ddc13",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 5. Alice sends coins to Bob\n",
    "print(\"\\n4. Alice sends 5 coin to Bob...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create transaction object\n",
    "transaction = Transaction(\n",
    "    alice.get_public_key_pem(),\n",
    "    bob.get_public_key_pem(),\n",
    "    5\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Prepare transaction data for signing\n",
    "tx_data = {\n",
    "    'sender': alice.get_public_key_pem(),\n",
    "    'receiver': bob.get_public_key_pem(), \n",
    "    'amount': 5\n",
    "}\n",
    "# Alice signs the transaction with her private key\n",
    "signature = alice.sign_transaction(tx_data, transaction.timestamp)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Attach the signature to the transaction \n",
    "transaction.signature = signature\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Signature created: {signature[:50]}...\")\n",
    "print(f\"Is transaction valid? {transaction.is_valid()}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add the transaction to the blockchain\n",
    "if blockchain.add_transaction(transaction):\n",
    "    # Update balances (simplified logic for demonstration)\n",
    "    alice.balance -= 5\n",
    "    bob.balance += 5\n",
    "    print(\"Transaction accepted!\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Transaction rejected!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1af9a511",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5. Final Audit\n",
    "Finally, we check:\n",
    "1.  **Balances**: Alice should have less, Bob should have more.\n",
    "2.  **Chain Integrity**: `is_chain_valid()` re-calculates all hashes to ensure no block was modified.\n",
    "3.  **Ledger Display**: We print the full chain to see the blocks and their hashes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "556fdf71",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 6. Show final balances\n",
    "print(f\"\\n6. Final balances:\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Alice: {alice.balance} coin\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Bob: {bob.balance} coin\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 7. Verify blockchain integrity\n",
    "# Checks if hashes link correctly and if data has been tampered\n",
    "print(\"\\n7. Verifying blockchain integrity...\")\n",
    "blockchain.is_chain_valid()\n",
    "\n",
    "# 8. Display the entire blockchain structure\n",
    "print(\"\\n8. Blockchain created:\")\n",
    "blockchain.display_chain()"
   ]
  }
 ],
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c113ab81",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6. Attack Simulation (Tampering Detection)\n",
    "We simulate an attacker intercepting a valid transaction and modifying the amount from 5 coins to 10 coins.\n",
    "Because the transaction signature was generated for the original amount (5), changing the amount invalidates the signature.\n",
    "The blockchain should detect this tampering and reject the malicious transaction."
   ]
  },
